A time and place is yet to be set for the executions. But General Pastika says they shouldn't be carried out in Bali. 

‘If it's possible, please not in Bali, just somewhere else," he told reporters, without giving his reasons.

‘I think they want Bali to keep in harmony, remain safe, remain peaceful. So if possible, not in Bali, please.’

It’s a change of tact for General Pastika who when testifying against members of the Bali Nine in a 2007 challenge of their death sentences described drug traffickers as ‘mass murderers’ who were deserving of death. 

