Sukumaran is only a year away from completing his Bachelor of Fine Arts through Monash University, and along with Chan has aided the introduction of cooking, philosophy and psychology lessons and a first aid course.

Bali locals have made a show of support, coming out to buy Sukumaran's art in the wake of his rejected clemency appeal. 

His mother made an emotional appeal on Saturday, speaking of how sorry her son was and how much he had changed as an individual.

'No mother should have to go through this, it's killing us. Please, something has to be done, please help,' Channel Seven reported Mrs Sukumaran as saying.

